        </marker>
      </defs>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="options">
    <div class="option"><span>1)</span> 13/11 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>2)</span> 13/10 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>3)</span> 10/13 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>4)</span> 11/13 m/s²</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q6 — wedge problem -->
<div class="q-block jee-main">
  <div class="q-number">Q 6 &nbsp;<span class="section-label jee-main-label">JEE Main</span><span class="level-badge lv2">Level 2</span></div>
  <div class="q-text">
    Consider the situation as shown in the figure. All surfaces are smooth. The string and the pulley are light. Find the magnitude of acceleration of the two blocks.
    (a = 53°, θ = 37°; wedge sides: 3 m, 4 m, 5 m; m₁ = 2 kg on one face, m₂ = 2 kg on other face)
  </div>
  <div class="diagram-box">
    <svg width="290" height="190" viewBox="0 0 290 190">
      <!-- double-faced wedge -->
      <polygon points="145,20 40,170 250,170" fill="#fce4ec" stroke="#c62828" stroke-width="2"/>
      <!-- left face label -->
      <text x="68" y="105" fill="#880e4f" font-size="10" transform="rotate(54,95,100)">3 m</text>
      <text x="178" y="115" fill="#880e4f" font-size="10" transform="rotate(-37,200,110)">4 m</text>
      <text x="115" y="183" fill="#555" font-size="10">5 m</text>
      <!-- angle labels -->
      <text x="55" y="162" fill="#1a237e" font-size="10">53°</text>
      <text x="210" y="162" fill="#1a237e" font-size="10">37°</text>
      <!-- m1 on left face -->
      <rect x="68" y="108" width="30" height="24" rx="3" fill="#7b1fa2" stroke="#4a148c" stroke-width="1.5" transform="rotate(54,83,120)"/>
      <text x="72" y="123" fill="white" font-size="10" font-weight="bold">2kg</text>
      <!-- m2 on right face -->
      <rect x="190" y="112" width="30" height="24" rx="3" fill="#283593" stroke="#1a237e" stroke-width="1.5" transform="rotate(-37,205,124)"/>
      <text x="193" y="127" fill="white" font-size="10" font-weight="bold">2kg</text>
      <!-- string over apex -->
      <line x1="82" y1="110" x2="145" y2="20" stroke="#333" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
      <line x1="145" y1="20" x2="205" y2="115" stroke="#333" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
      <circle cx="145" cy="20" r="7" fill="#ffa726" stroke="#e65100" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <!-- acc arrows -->
      <line x1="90" y1="135" x2="75" y2="148" stroke="#d32f2f" stroke-width="1.8" marker-end="url(#arr3)"/>
      <text x="60" y="148" fill="#d32f2f" font-size="9">a</text>
      <defs>
        <marker id="arr3" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="3" refY="3" orient="auto">
          <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#d32f2f"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="options">
    <div class="option"><span>1)</span> 8/7 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>2)</span> 8/4 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>3)</span> 8/9 m/s²</div>
    <div class="option"><span>4)</span> 8/10 m/s²</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q7 -->
<div class="q-block jee-main">
  <div class="q-number">Q 7 &nbsp;<span class="section-label jee-main-label">JEE Main</span><span class="level-badge lv3">Level 3</span></div>
  <div class="q-text">
    In figure a body of mass m₁ (m₁ = 2 kg) on a smooth inclined surface is connected to a body of mass m₂ (m₂ = 4 kg). The pulley is massless and frictionless. An upward force F = 12 N acts on the body m₂ which has downward acceleration 5.5 m/s². Find the tension in the connecting cord.
  </div>
  <div class="diagram-box">
    <svg width="280" height="200" viewBox="0 0 280 200">
      <!-- incline -->
      <polygon points="20,170 200,170 200,50" fill="#e8f5e9" stroke="#2e7d32" stroke-width="2"/>
      <text x="38" y="162" fill="#2e7d32" font-size="11">θ</text>
      <!-- m1 on slope -->
      <rect x="105" y="100" width="36" height="28" rx="3" fill="#388e3c" stroke="#1b5e20" stroke-width="1.5" transform="rotate(-27,123,114)"/>
      <text x="113" y="117" fill="white" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">m₁</text>
      <text x="113" y="128" fill="white" font-size="8">2 kg</text>
      <!-- pulley -->
      <circle cx="200" cy="50" r="10" fill="#ffa726" stroke="#e65100" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <!-- string -->
      <line x1="140" y1="100" x2="200" y2="50" stroke="#333" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
      <line x1="200" y1="60" x2="200" y2="120" stroke="#333" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <text x="205" y="90" fill="#555" font-size="10">T</text>
      <!-- m2 hanging -->
      <rect x="185" y="120" width="30" height="26" rx="3" fill="#1565c0" stroke="#0d47a1" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <text x="190" y="136" fill="white" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">m₂</text>
      <text x="189" y="148" fill="white" font-size="8">4 kg</text>
      <!-- F arrow up -->
      <line x1="200" y1="118" x2="200" y2="98" stroke="#7b1fa2" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrF)"/>
      <text x="205" y="108" fill="#7b1fa2" font-size="10">F=12N</text>
      <!-- a arrow down -->
      <line x1="200" y1="148" x2="200" y2="165" stroke="#d32f2f" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr4)"/>
      <text x="205" y="163" fill="#d32f2f" font-size="10">a↓</text>
      <!-- label -->
      <text x="20" y="190" fill="#555" font-size="9">m₁=2 kg (on slope), m₂=4 kg (hanging), F=12 N upward</text>
      <defs>
        <marker id="arr4" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="3" refY="3" orient="auto">
          <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#d32f2f"/>
        </marker>
        <marker id="arrF" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="3" refY="3" orient="auto">
          <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#7b1fa2"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="options">
    <div class="option"><span>1)</span> 2.6 N</div>
    <div class="option"><span>2)</span> 5.2 N</div>
    <div class="option"><span>3)</span> 6.2 N</div>
    <div class="option"><span>4)</span> 3.7 N</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q8 — wedge + block accelerating -->
<div class="q-block jee-main">
  <div class="q-number">Q 8 &nbsp;<span class="section-label jee-main-label">JEE Main</span><span class="level-badge lv4">Level 4</span></div>
  <div class="q-text">
    All surfaces are smooth. The acceleration of mass m relative to wedge is:
